&lt;p&gt;At Mizzen+Main, we believe what we wear to work reflects what we think of work. And we think work is fun. We think it’s a place of joy, collaboration, discipline, laughter,the ups and downs, and everything in between all of those things. That’s why we make clothes that make people comfortable. We make clothes that let people breathe and stretch and move and think. We make clothes that let them work. And we have a good time doing it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2012 with the belief that there is a better way, Mizzen+Main is a premium men’s brand with product rooted in performance fabrics and tailored silhouettes. Mizzen+Main is a multi-channel brand, comprised of our Ecommerce site, Retail Stores, and Wholesale Partners across the US, with our headquarters in Dallas, Texas. Our Values are simple and guide everything we do: We Have Commitments, We Think Big, We Act as Owners, We’re People Too, and We Never Settle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Systems Administrator, you’ll keep our business systems running smoothly through the administration, performance, and ongoing evolution of our ERP platform and connected applications. You’ll partner across teams to troubleshoot issues, improve workflows, and support the integrations and upgrades that help our business move with speed and confidence. You’ll also be a go‑to resource for user support, access management, and device setup across both our office and retail environments. If you love solving problems, making systems better, and helping people do their best work, you’ll feel right at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A DAY IN THE LIFE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and configure the ERP platform (NetSuite preferred), including roles, permissions, workflows, saved searches, and data governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain system integrity through audits, documentation, and proactive monitoring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support integrations between ERP and other business applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross‑functional teams to troubleshoot issues, optimize processes, and support new functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with system upgrades, enhancements, and testing cycles. Monitor and manage patches and OS updates as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop system integrations and maintain existing ones, using the DellBoomi SaaS platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage core business applications, user provisioning, and system access controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation for systems, integrations, and standard operating procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor system performance and escalate issues appropriately.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide user support for hardware, software, and account issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with IT service providers to support users in the office and retail stores.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with onboarding/offboarding tasks and device setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help users understand system changes, new features, or updated workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain confidentiality regarding employee, company and customer information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of system technology best practices and changing technologies for business technology enhancements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
